                  </hi>. I am a widow, and live in Stratford-grove, Essex. My husband died four months ago—the prisoner was in his employment, and con<lb></lb>tinued in mine afterwards—he received money on my account—at my hus<lb></lb>band's death, I sent him to a Mr. Flax ton, who was indebted to my husband—he said he had seen Mr. Flaxton, and that he would call on me in a few days—the amount of his bill was 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I never received any part of it—the prisoner absconded as soon as it was found out—I had another cus<lb></lb>tomer named Coates, part of his bill was due before my husband's death—I gave the prisoner in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q,</hi> He came to yon again afterwards? <hi rend="italic">A,</hi> Yes, and said he was very sorry for it—I am left sole executrix of my hus<lb></lb>band's affairs—I carry on the business of a furrier—part of Mr. Coatts's debt, to the amount of 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., occurred since my. husband's death—the prisoner worked for me twelve months at 22<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a week.</p>
